    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical History</head>
      <p>Jules François Felix Fleury-Husson (1820-1889) was a French art critic and author who wrote under the pen name Champfleury.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The<emph render="bold"> Champfleury Collection</emph> is a set of bound items,  including a handwritten manuscript copy of "Voyage autour de ma bibliothèque" ("Journey Around my Library"), an essay by Champfleury. The text of the essay was published in 1903 in <emph render="italic">Champfleury inédit</emph>,
 edited by Paul Eudel. </p><p>The collection also includes a letter sent to Paul Eudel in 1890 by the author Jules Troubat, who was a personal friend of Champfleury.</p>
      </scopecontent>
